@page "/docs/guides/use-tweakcn-themes"
@namespace Lumeo.Docs.Pages.Docs

<PageTitle>Use tweakcn themes — Lumeo</PageTitle>

<Container MaxWidth="3xl" Padding="0" Center="false">
<Stack Gap="10">

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <Heading Level="1" Size="3xl">Use tweakcn themes</Heading>
        <Lumeo.Text Size="base" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
            <Lumeo.Link Href="https://tweakcn.com" Class="text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">tweakcn</Lumeo.Link>
            is a visual theme editor for shadcn/ui — pick colors and radii in a browser UI, copy the generated CSS, paste it into your stylesheet. Because Lumeo's CSS reads through the same
            <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--primary</code>,
            <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--radius</code>, and
            <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--background</code> variable names, a tweakcn export drops straight in. No wrapper, no mapping layer.
        </Lumeo.Text>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <Heading Level="2">Steps</Heading>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3">1 — Generate the theme</Heading>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
                Go to <Lumeo.Link Href="https://tweakcn.com" Class="text-foreground underline underline-offset-4 hover:text-muted-foreground transition-colors">tweakcn.com</Lumeo.Link>,
                dial in your colors and corner radii, then click <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Code / Export</strong>.
                Choose <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">OKLCH</strong> and <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Tailwind v4</strong>. Copy the
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">:root</code> and
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">.dark</code> blocks.
            </Lumeo.Text>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3">2 — Confirm the Lumeo import is present</Heading>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
                Your global stylesheet must import Lumeo's CSS. The default project setup already does this — check for the line below in
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">wwwroot/css/app.css</code>
                (or wherever you load styles):
            </Lumeo.Text>
            <pre class="code-block rounded-lg border border-border/40 bg-muted px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-foreground whitespace-pre overflow-x-auto">@_import</pre>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3">3 — Paste the theme blocks after the import</Heading>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
                Paste both blocks (<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">:root</code> and
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">.dark</code>) into the same stylesheet,
                <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">after</strong> the Lumeo import line. Order matters for
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--radius</code> and
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--shadow-*</code> — Lumeo declares those too, so they must be overridden later in the cascade. Colors (like
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--primary</code>) work regardless of order.
            </Lumeo.Text>
            <pre class="code-block rounded-lg border border-border/40 bg-muted px-4 py-3 font-mono text-xs text-foreground whitespace-pre overflow-x-auto">@_paste</pre>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3">4 — Dark mode is wired automatically</Heading>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
                Lumeo's <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">ThemeService</code> toggles the
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">.dark</code> class on
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">&lt;html&gt;</code>, which is exactly the selector tweakcn targets. No extra setup needed — light and dark switch as expected.
            </Lumeo.Text>
        </Stack>

        <Stack Gap="3">
            <Heading Level="3">5 — Rebuild CSS</Heading>
            <Lumeo.Text Size="sm" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
                If you use a Tailwind build step (e.g. the Lumeo PostCSS preset or
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">tailwindcss --watch</code>), let it rebuild so the new custom-property values are picked up. For plain CSS imports, a browser refresh is enough.
            </Lumeo.Text>
        </Stack>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <Heading Level="2">What maps</Heading>
        <Lumeo.Text Size="base" Color="muted" Leading="relaxed">
            Every token tweakcn emits flows into Lumeo. The full coverage:
        </Lumeo.Text>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground list-disc list-inside">
            <li><strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Color surface</strong> — <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">background</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">foreground</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">card</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">popover</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">primary</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">secondary</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">muted</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">accent</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">destructive</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">border</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">input</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">ring</code>.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Charts</strong> — <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">chart-1</code> through <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">chart-5</code>.</li>
            <li><strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Sidebar</strong> — the full sidebar token set (<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">sidebar-background</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">sidebar-primary</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">sidebar-accent</code>, etc.).</li>
            <li><strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Corner radii</strong> — <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--radius</code> propagates to all components via <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">calc(var(--radius) * …)</code>.</li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <Heading Level="2">Caveats</Heading>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-muted-foreground list-disc list-inside">
            <li>
                <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Paste order matters for radius and shadows.</strong>
                <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--radius</code> and <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--shadow-*</code> are declared by Lumeo, so the tweakcn block must come <em class="not-italic font-medium text-foreground">after</em> the Lumeo import (unlayered) to win the cascade. Color tokens don't have this constraint.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Fonts are partial.</strong>
                Only <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--font-sans</code> is read by Lumeo's CSS. <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--font-serif</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--font-mono</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--tracking-*</code>, and <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--spacing</code> are emitted by tweakcn but have no effect on Lumeo components.
            </li>
            <li>
                <strong class="text-foreground font-medium">Lumeo-only tokens keep their defaults.</strong>
                Semantic tokens specific to Lumeo — <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--success</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--warning</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--info</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--positive</code>, <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">--rating</code>, and their <code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">-light</code>/<code class="rounded bg-muted px-1.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-mono text-foreground">-text</code> variants — are not emitted by tweakcn and keep their Lumeo defaults. Override them manually if needed.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

    <Separator Class="my-4" />

    <Stack Gap="4">
        <Heading Level="2">See also</Heading>
        <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm">
            <li><a class="text-primary hover:underline" href="docs/theme-overrides">Theme Overrides</a> — fine-grained token overrides without a third-party editor.</li>
            <li><a class="text-primary hover:underline" href="docs/tweakcn">Theming with tweakcn</a> — reference page for tweakcn token coverage.</li>
            <li><a class="text-primary hover:underline" href="docs/services/theme">Theme Service</a> — programmatic light/dark switching.</li>
        </ul>
    </Stack>

</Stack>
</Container>

@code {
    private const string _import = @"/* app.css */
@@import ""_content/Lumeo/css/lumeo.css"";";

    private const string _paste = @"/* app.css */
@@import ""_content/Lumeo/css/lumeo.css"";

/* tweakcn export — paste AFTER the Lumeo import */
:root {
  --background: oklch(1 0 0);
  --foreground: oklch(0.145 0 0);
  --primary: oklch(0.556 0.241 292.9);
  --radius: 1.4rem;
  /* … rest of tweakcn output … */
}

.dark {
  --background: oklch(0.145 0 0);
  --foreground: oklch(0.985 0 0);
  --primary: oklch(0.556 0.241 292.9);
  /* … */
}";
}
